{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-wiki-post-js","path":"/HOF_Framework/1-getting-started","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<div class=\"table-of-contents\">\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"#preamble\">Preamble</a></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"#requirements\">Requirements</a></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"#building-your-first-hof-form\">Building your first hof form</a></p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#installing-the-hof-cli\">Installing the hof cli</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#creating-your-first-form\">Creating your first form</a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<h2 id=\"preamble\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#preamble\" aria-label=\"preamble permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Preamble</h2>\n<p>It is expected when following these guides that you have a basic knowledge of unix terminals and are running OSX or a Linux operating system.</p>\n<p>It is also expected that you have a working knowledge of javascript and node.js and are comfortable installing packages from npm. You should also be comfortable working with git.</p>\n<p>This documentation is written with the assumption that you are using the latest versions of hof modules. Not all of this documentation will be relevant if you are not using the latest versions.</p>\n<h2 id=\"requirements\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#requirements\" aria-label=\"requirements permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Requirements</h2>\n<p>hof is built in <a href=\"https://nodejs.org/en/\">node.js</a>, and so you'll need that installed first. At present all versions 4 and above are supported, although it is recommended that you use the <a href=\"https://github.com/nodejs/LTS#lts-schedule\">latest LTS version</a>.</p>\n<p>hof also requires npm version 3 or greater. You can check your installed version by running <code class=\"language-jstext\">npm -v</code> and update to the latest version by running <code class=\"language-jstext\">npm install -g npm@latest</code>.</p>\n<p>To run hof apps locally for development you will either need a local instance of redis running, or docker installed.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>How to <a href=\"https://medium.com/@petehouston/install-and-config-redis-on-mac-os-x-via-homebrew-eb8df9a4f298#.jcwwhv7oz\">install redis on OSX</a></li>\n<li>How to <a href=\"https://docs.docker.com/docker-for-mac/install/#install-and-run-docker-for-mac\">install docker on OSX</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"building-your-first-hof-form\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#building-your-first-hof-form\" aria-label=\"building your first hof form permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Building your first hof form</h2>\n<p>The fastest way to create a new hof app is to use the <a href=\"https://npmjs.com/hof-generator\">hof command line generator</a>. This will automatically create a bare-bones hof form in a directory of your choice.</p>\n<h3 id=\"installing-the-hof-cli\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#installing-the-hof-cli\" aria-label=\"installing the hof cli permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Installing the hof cli</h3>\n<p>Install the cli from npm:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre style=\"counter-reset: linenumber NaN\" class=\"language-jstext line-numbers\"><code class=\"language-jstext\">npm install -g hof-generator</code><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"line-numbers-rows\" style=\"white-space: normal; width: auto; left: 0;\"><span></span></span></pre></div>\n<h3 id=\"creating-your-first-form\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#creating-your-first-form\" aria-label=\"creating your first form permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Creating your first form</h3>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre style=\"counter-reset: linenumber NaN\" class=\"language-jstext line-numbers\"><code class=\"language-jstext\">mkdir my-hof-form\ncd my-hof-form\nhof init</code><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"line-numbers-rows\" style=\"white-space: normal; width: auto; left: 0;\"><span></span><span></span><span></span></span></pre></div>\n<p>This will generate a brand new hof app in the directory you created.</p>\n<p>You can then start your app by running <code class=\"language-jstext\">docker-compose up</code> or <code class=\"language-jstext\">npm start</code> (needs local redis instance).</p>\n<p>If you open <a href=\"http://localhost:8080/my-hof-form\">http://localhost:8080/my-hof-form</a> in a browser then you should see your app. It should look something like this:</p>\n<p><img src=\"../images/getting-started.png\" alt=\"\"></p>","frontmatter":{"path":"/1-getting-started","title":"— Getting Started —","tags":null}}},"pageContext":{"title":"— Getting Started —","slug":"/HOF_Framework/getting-started/","tags":null,"breadcrumb":{"location":"/HOF_Framework/1-getting-started","crumbs":[{"pathname":"/","crumbLabel":"Home"},{"pathname":"/HOF_Framework","crumbLabel":"HOF_Framework"},{"pathname":"/HOF_Framework/1-getting-started","crumbLabel":"1-getting-started"}]}}},"staticQueryHashes":["2744294623","3649515864","3684199878"]}